member.name: M:CyberSource.Clients.AppSettings.GetSetting(System.String,System.String,System.String)
member.summary:
Gets the specified setting from the config file.
Search order is as follows: cybs.value_of_merchantID.value_of_key value_of_merchantID.value_of_key cybs.value_of_key value_of_key
The ones without the cybs prefix are supported only for backwards-compatibility.
You can specify merchantID-specific settings by prefixing them with the merchantID. For example: cybs.merchant1.keysDir will apply only to merchant1. cybs.keysDir will apply to all other merchants.
Please note that the following settings cannot be merchant-specific: merchantID proxyURL proxyUser proxyPassword
There can therefore only be one set of proxy server settings for all merchant ids. The reason being the Proxy object, if needed, is initialized during start-up. It would be expensive to keep creating one for each request.
If merchantID is set in the request, it overrides the one in the config file.
member.param: merchant id whose key is being requested
key of the setting being requested
value returned if none is found in the config file.
member.returns: value read from the config file, or the value of defaultVal if none was found.

member.name: M:CyberSource.Clients.AppSettings.GetBoolSetting(System.String,System.String)
member.summary: Gets the specified boolean setting from the config file.
member.param: merchant id whose key is being requested
key of the setting being requested

member.name: M:CyberSource.Clients.AppSettings.GetIntSetting(System.String,System.String)
member.summary: Gets the specified integer setting from the config file.
member.param: merchant id whose key is being requested
key of the setting being requested
member.returns: integer value read from the config file. A value of -1 means the key was not found.
